subSubSection.paragraph:
Mesothorax.
Preepisternal plate narrow, arrow-shaped (
Fig. 33
), weakly produced sidewards, bare; median longitudinal portion broad, bearing sparse long setae in ventral view, widely attaching metaventral process. Lateral margin of elytron with bead throughout, very narrowly explanate on posterior half (
Fig. 1
). Outer bare portion of epipleuron (= “pseudepipleuron”) about 0.3× as wide as inner pubescent portion (= “epipleuron”) in basal third, about 0.7× as wide as inner pubescent portion in distal two-thirds.
